20:53.578 --> 20:54.886
Baby, you saved my life.

20:55.337 --> 20:56.407
I'm glad you're looking so good.

20:56.408 --> 20:57.780
Hey, Pam. Happy Birthday.

20:58.349 --> 21:00.190
Thank you, sweetheart. You
know Juliette Barnes?

21:00.191 --> 21:01.798
Miss Tillis, it is such
an honor to meet you.

21:01.799 --> 21:04.105
I'm a huge fan. Thank you for coming.
Thank you.

21:05.035 --> 21:06.608
She's nicer than I heard she was.

21:11.972 --> 21:13.747
Thank you guys so much for coming.

21:13.748 --> 21:15.571
It's so great to see how
many people love Deacon

21:15.572 --> 21:16.784
as much as I do.

21:20.788 --> 21:24.419
And a little fun fact is
Deacon's got so much talent,

21:24.420 --> 21:26.387
it couldn't all be contained
in one generation.

21:26.388 --> 21:28.052
So, ladies and gentlemen, give it up

21:28.053 --> 21:30.708
for Deacon's niece Scarlett O'Connor

21:30.709 --> 21:32.049
and Gunnar Scott.

21:37.683 --> 21:38.815
Oh, thank you.

21:40.130 --> 21:42.113
Deacon, I'm sorry for tricking
you into coming out here,

21:42.114 --> 21:43.439
